<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>

<p>There are several ways, see below, the options</p>

<ul>
  <li>Debian, Ubuntu and Linux Mint</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">wget https://github.com/cjbassi/gotop/releases/download/3.0.0/gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.deb
<span class="nb">sudo </span>dpkg <span class="nt">-i</span> gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.deb</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>RedHat, CentOS e Fedora</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">wget https://github.com/cjbassi/gotop/releases/download/3.0.0/gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.rpm
<span class="nb">sudo </span>rpm <span class="nt">-ivh</span> gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.rpm</code></pre></figure>

<ul>
  <li>Arch Linux via AUR (gotop, gotop-bin, ou gotop-git)</li>
  <li>FreeBSD</li>
</ul>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">pkg <span class="nb">install </span>gotop</code></pre></figure>

<p>Or for any distro, download with wget</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">wget https://github.com/cjbassi/gotop/releases/download/3.0.0/gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.tgz</code></pre></figure>

<!-- QUADRADO -->
<script async="" src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>

<p><ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:inline-block;width:336px;height:280px" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2838251107855362" data-ad-slot="5351066970"></ins>
<script>
(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></p>

<p>or with Go itself if you have installed</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">go get github.com/cjbassi/gotop</code></pre></figure>

<p>Unzip the TGZ</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">tar </span>zxvf gotop_3.0.0_linux_amd64.tgz</code></pre></figure>

