<p>You can already run with the command: <code class="highlighter-rouge">./gotop</code> and if you want it to be executed via command, use your personal dir without sudo, thatâ€™s how I did it!</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">mkdir</span> <span class="nt">-p</span> ~/.local/bin
<span class="nb">mv </span>gotop ~/.local/bin/
<span class="c"># If this directory is not your PATH, include</span>
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'PATH="${PATH}:$HOME/.local/bin/"'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.bashrc
<span class="nb">source</span> ~/.bashrc
gotop</code></pre></figure>

<p>See help for key shortcuts: <code class="highlighter-rouge">gotop --help</code></p>

<p>Official page gotop: <a href="https://github.com/cjbassi/gotop">https://github.com/cjbassi/gotop</a>
